name: phenyl_benzoate
source: Aldrich Chemical Company; Aldrich Catalog-Handbook of Fine Chemicals; Milwaukee; WI; 1984.
Reason: 1,2-propanediol base, with a melting point around 50 degrees Celsius. The phenyl group introduces a rigid structure and additional molecular weight, estimated at +20 degrees Celsius. The benzene ring introduces additional pi-pi interactions, estimated at +10 degrees Celsius. The methoxy group introduces additional hydrogen bonding potential, estimated at +5 degrees Celsius. The carbamate group introduces additional hydrogen bonding, estimated at +5 degrees Celsius.
